special_powers.name: BASIC PROGRAMMING
special_powers.description: When Ultron-7 has no action tokens, its actions don't count against your action total. When Ultron-7 begins or ends a non-free action adjacent to a friendly character whose name includes Ultron, it can use Willpower that action.

special_powers.name: IMMOBILIZATION RAY

special_powers.name: ALPHA PRIMITIVES, ATTACK!

special_powers.name: ULTRON IMPERATIVE
special_powers.description: When Ultron-18.2 would be KO'd, you may choose a friendly character with the Robot keyword and a lower point value. If you do, turn Ultron-18.2 to his first KO click, roll a d6 that can't be rerolled and heal him of that much damage. After you do, KO the chosen character.

special_powers.name: CONTROL ARMOR AND S.K.I.N.
special_powers.description: Ultron-18.2 can use Mind Control and Running Shot. He can use Mind Control as a free action, but only to target characters with the Armor or Robot keyword. Characters he hits using Mind Control modify their combat values by +1 during your turn and -1 during their next turn.

special_powers.name: THE SONS OF YINSEN FOLLOW ME ANYWHERE!

special_powers.name: SHALL WE PLAY A GAME?
special_powers.description: Give Grandmaster a free action when he has 2 action tokens and choose an opposing character within range and line of fire. That character's player must guess the printed speed, attack, defense, and damage values of the chosen character's next click, then deal the chosen character 1 unavoidable damage. If the opponent guessed all 4 values correctly, immediately heal that character of 2 damage. If the opponent guesses all 4 values incorrectly, deal that character an additional 1 unavoidable damage.

special_powers.name: MY VERSION OF "FAIR PLAY"
special_powers.description: Grandmaster can use Perplex and Probability Control. Opposing characters can't use Probability Control unless a character friendly to Grandmaster has used Probability Control this turn.

special_powers.name: THE POWER OF GRAVITON, LORD OF THE FUNDAMENTAL FORCES
special_powers.description: Graviton can use Incapacitate. When he does, he may deal damage equal to his printed damage value split among the hit targets.

special_powers.name: TOTAL CONTROL OF GRAVITONS AND ANTI-GRAVITONS
special_powers.description: Graviton can use Telekinesis. If he uses Telekinesis to move an opposing character, he may treat that character as friendly when he does. If he has no action tokens, he may use Telekinesis as a free action, but only to target an object.

special_powers.name: DEBRIS SHIELD
special_powers.description: Graviton can use Energy Shield/Deflection and Toughness.

special_powers.name: THE POWER OF GRAVITY GONE WILD
special_powers.description: Opposing characters who begin an action within 5 squares replace their speed value with 3 and it is locked.

special_powers.name: MY KNIGHTS OF WUNDAGORE, EVOLVED FROM ANIMALS
special_powers.description: Give High Evolutionary a power action. Place a Knight of Wundagore token as described on this card in an adjacent square. The opponent scores 15 points for each Kight of Wundagore KO'd.

special_powers.name: EVOLVED MYSELF TO A HIGHER ENTITY
special_powers.description: When this click is first revealed, stop turning the dial. For the rest of the game, even if this power is lost, High Evolutionary has "giant damage symbol" and can use the Power Cosmic team ability. This power can't be ignored.

special_powers.name: EVOLVE OTHERS AT WILL
special_powers.description: High Evolutionary can use Perplex. When he does and actions resolve, modify two combat values on the same target, each by +1 or -1. To determine the combat vlaues, roll 2d6 and modify the indicated combat value: 1 = Range, 2 = Speed, 3 = Attack, 4 = Defense, 5 = Damage, 6 = Choose

When the Time Bubble is on the map and Kang the Conqueror would take damage, you may instead place him in the square with the Time Bubble, deal him 1 unavoidable damage, and attach the Time Bubble to him.
